Our primary bathroom before & after ~ someday I’ll get around to documenting it on the blog! 🤦🏼‍♀️Our window covering was installed several months ago and I forgot to share with you! It’s so 😍 pretty! And I don’t think I ever shared our shower glass window area either 😊when I designed the shower I opted for minimal glass for privacy and less cleaning ~ I love how unique it is and how it doesn’t look like every other shower! The window we created let’s in the perfect amount of light combined with the shower door which allows for a steam shower experience similar to a spa shower which is exactly what I was going for! Would you do something unconventional like this?! My design advice: Update your home how YOU want to ~ do things that will bring you happiness and joy, not just because it’s the latest trend or “in” thing! #beforeandafter #homerenovation #bathroomdesign #bathroomremodel #bathroominspiration #bathroomideas #bathroombeforeandafter

Breakfast nook to keeping room! I’ve been wanting to try this for awhile now! I watched an episode of In with the Old recently and learned all about keeping rooms! I decided I needed one 😊& it would be perfect adjacent to our kitchen since don’t need 2 dining areas! It’s the perfect place for to relax and read, enjoy coffee in the morning or a glass of wine in the evening…for family and friends to gather and my girls to hang while I’m cooking. I shopped my home and loved furniture around to see if I liked it and I can say the photos and videos don’t do it justice! It’s so welcoming and cozy! Would you give a keeping room a try? #keepingroom #homemakeover #shopyourhome #modernclassicinterior #modernclassicdesign #roomandboard

It doesn’t take a lot! And on another note it feels so good to be home after a fun vacation ~ truly nothing ever beats being home! 💗

Eras Tour: LA 8/9 💙we were ready…1989 outfits & a New Romantics bracelet…manifesting that it would happen. she stepped out in that gorgeous blue dress during Enchanted and we crossed our fingers so tight! When she announced 1989 Taylor’s Version everyone went nuts including us! It was truly the most magical & beautiful experience and a night that we will never forget. Thank you @taylorswift for bringing so much happiness, joy and love to your fans. for giving us the opportunity to bond with our loved ones and the strangers around us, making lifetime memories 💙#erastour

We are heartbroken 💔 We will miss you and love you forever Mavis. You brought us so much joy and happiness. It was too soon, unexpected and so unfair. You were such a good girl and we are so fortunate to have made so many wonderful memories with you. We know you crossed the rainbow 🌈 bridge and are comfortable now and in peace.❤️

Highlights from our fall break in New England (one of the many perks of modified year round school is being able to go on fun trips without the summer crowds) 
🍁Woodstock
🍎Stowe
🎃Salem
🌊Gloucester 
📍Boston 
We enjoyed all the fall things, peeping the leaves, apple picking, maple syrup tasting, long walks in gorgeous fall weather, soaked in the history, visited a beautiful historic library & bought a couple of vintage books, went to all of our fav spots to grab yummy food and treats and spent quality time together as a family 🧡I cherish these times together because they are growing up so fast🧡
#newenglandlife #stowevermont  #newengland #vermontfall #fallinvermont #fallinnewengland #fallaesthetic #falltravel

What a year…so many core memories created, unforgettable experiences & beautiful moments captured coupled with health challenges & heartbreak that led to feelings of sadness, grief & disappointment. through it all we have grown stronger and we hope that 2024 brings health, happiness & joy ~ more fun creating new memories while honoring our traditions. And we wish the same for all of you!! I will forever have a grateful heart, especially for this community that has given me the opportunity to be more present & available to my family - your support means so much ♥️ Remember there will always be good days and hard days. Creating a life you truly love is a gift to your family & friends and makes those hard days a little brighter and the good days that much better ✨As you head into the new year think about what makes you happy, what & who brings you joy & how you can bring more of that positive energy into 2024!!
✌🏻out 2023…2024 LET’S GO 🥳
#newyearsrecap #newyearseve2023
